```

## Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] `useSessionStatus` accepts `string | null` as its first parameter type
- [ ] When called with `null`, no call to `transport.getSession` occurs
- [ ] When called with a non-empty string, `transport.getSession` is called normally
- [ ] `updateSession` returns early (no-op) when `sessionId` is null
- [ ] TypeScript compiles without errors after the change
- [ ] The `enabled: !!sessionId` guard is present in the `useQuery` call

